    "16001": "The riser height (%1!s!) of this stair is out of the range specified in the stair style: it must be between minimum height (%2!s!), and maximum height (%3!s!).",
    "16002": "• In Options>AEC Object Settings>Stair Settings, set Calculator Limits to Relaxed.&#10;• In the Style Manager>Design Rules, change the Riser Height value for Minimum Slope or Maximum Slope. &#10;• Change the stair size to comply with the current design rules of the stair style.",
    "16003": "The tread depth (%1!s!) of this stair is out of the range specified in the stair style: it must be between minimum depth (%2!s!), and maximum depth (%3!s!).",
    "16004": "• In Options>AEC Object Settings>Stair Settings, set Calculator Limits to Relaxed.&#10;• In Style Manager>Design Rules, change the Tread Depth value for Minimum Slope or Maximum Slope. &#10;• Change the stair size to comply with the current design rules of the stair style.",
    "16005": "The riser height and tread depth of this stair do not comply with the calculator rule specified in the stair style: the formula in the Style Manager.",
    "16006": "• In Options>AEC Object Settings>Stair Settings, set Calculator Limits to Relaxed.&#10;• In the Style Manager>Design Rules, change the Riser Height or Tread Depth value for Minimum Slope or Maximum Slope. &#10;• Change the stair size to comply with the current design rules of the stair style.",
    "16007": "Error occured when creating stair riser components.",
    "16008": "• In the Style Manager, under Stringer tab,modify the width of the stringer;&#10;• Click the Edit Edges control, and then drag the Flight Width control to remove the intersection;&#10;• Change winder type of the stair to balance.",
